reviewText: 80-76%-perfect75-71%-awsome70-66%-good65-61%-Poor60-56%-awful1. The dudley boyz vs. La resistance for the tag team titles in a tables match- This was a good way to kick things off. Winners and new tag team champs the dudleys. Match Rating 7/10.2. Test vs Scott stiner- This was just another average match. I think i liked it a little more because i have liked stiner for a long time. Nothing horriable but still not great. Winner test. Match Rating 6/10.3. Randy Orton vs. Shawn Michales- I thought this was a great place to put this match. I really enjoyed this match. It was a good 19 minute match. There werent to many slow spots and some good action. Match Rating 9/10.4. Gal kim and molly holly vs. lita and trish- This was just your average womans match. To cool the crowd off after a good match. Non stop action through the whole match. Kane dosent even finish his entrence before shane came down with a chair and hit him like 8 times with it. Winner Kane. Match Rating 10/10.6. Y2J vs. Christian vs. Rob Van Dam for the ITC title- This was another good match. About 18 minutes of good soild action. Jim Ross and Jerry Lawer vs. the coach and al snow- I expected this match to be awful and it was. First problem was that there was no commantary. reviewText: This was an awesome ppv, my third fav. ppv of the year(1st being Vengeance and 2nd being WMXIX).  Here are the matches:WWE Handicap Table Match for the Tag Titles: Dudley Boyz vs. La Resistance and Rob Conway.  Good match, considering the Dudleyz haven't had a table match in a long time.  There were no special ways of eliminationg ppl thru those tables, but still a good match with the Dudleyz leaving the tag champs.  ***1/2(out of *****)Test vs. Scott Steiner.  This had been a fued that had gone on a long while, and this time if Scott won, he'd get Stacy, but if he lost, Test would have his services.  A good match, believe it or not, since Scott usually has bad matches, but this is one of Scott's best, even tho the match was 7 minutes long.  ***Shawn Michaels vs. Randy Orton.  Awesome match, this is Shawn's best match since his encounter with Jericho.  These guys really told a story in their match and showed their determination to win this match.  The match was brought down some however with Flair interfering a lot and Randy winning with a brass knucks shot to HBK.  But still an incredible match.  *****Trish Stratus and Lita vs. Molly Holly and Gail Kim.  Ok match, nothing real big happening, except it being Lita's return match.  Trish and Lita pull off the win with the Moonsault by Lita.  **Last Man Standing: Shane McMahon vs. Kane.  Brutal as hell.  The best Last man standing match I've ever seen.  This match is way better than their Ambulance match at Sur. Series, and these guys did just about everything to each other, and a shocking ending you'd have to see to believe.  *****IC Title - Jericho vs. RVD vs. Christian.  What was bad about this match was the crowd wasn't into it, basically got no reactions, which sucked, but the match itself was great.  Nowadays, you'd expect a match like this to last about 7 minutes, but these guys went about 20 minutes, and did what they could to show their stuff in this match, including one spot with all three men that was sick.  ****Raw Announcing Job on the line - Coach and Al Snow vs. JR and King.  I didn't even watch it, we all know this match is gonna be crap, even if Al and King can wrestle a bit.  But since I didn't watch it, I just won't rate it.World Title - Triple H vs. Goldberg.  If Goldberg loses, he's gone.  Boring match.  The crowd wasn't into it, and neither was I.  HHH basically did nothing but submissions, and Goldberg finished it off with his Spear and Jackhammer to get win and become the World Heavyweight Champion, much to the crowds' happiness.  **1/2.Easter Egg - At the main menu, highlight matches, and press left twice, and than down for a special music video of the Unforgiven matches.This is a great ppv, tho it should of had more extras.  Overall the ppv was one of their best this year, and one I'd recommend to anyone to buy.

reviewText: Table Match for the World Tag Team ChampionshipLa Resistance vs. Dudley BoyzGood opener.  Fairly unpredictable too.Scott Steiner vs. TestBetter than expected.  Decent wrestling in this one.Shawn Michaels vs. Randy OrtonNear classic except for the ridiculous ending.  I'm not sure why the writers opted out of a clean ending. However his attitude is more like late 90's WCW.  He's always in the main event and/or champion and it becomes stale.

reviewText: <50: Ask for a refund for not only your money, but also your time. [F]50-54: Mediocre & disappointing. [D] (EG: Judgment Day '03)55-59: Average. [C] (EG: Bad Blood '03)60-64: Worth A Watch. [C+] (EG: SummerSlam '03)65-69: Good event that was worth the money. [B] (EG: Royal Rumble '03)70-74: Very good. [B+] (EG: WrestleMania 19)75-79: Make sure you add this ppv to your video or dvd collection. [A] (EG: SummerSlam '02)80+ : Make sure that the video or dvd is locked in a safe & cannot be erased. Memorable. [A+]THE DUDLEY BOYZ defeated LA RESISTANCE & ROB CONWAY in a Tables Match to Win the World Tag-Team Titles: The Dudleyz are quickly becoming the warm-up act for the crowd, with the amount of pay-per-views they open. It makes sense I suppose. If this wasn't a tables match, it wouldn't have had many redeeming features & would have been pure monotony that we've seen many times before. With the stipulation, it was at least watchable. Conway took one hell of a bump through a table!!! The Dudleyz regain after 10 minutes. Match Rating...5TEST defeated SCOTT STEINER to Win the services of Steiner & Stacy Keibler: In yet another monotonous feud that has seemed like it has lasted forever, these 3 (Stacy's contribution to this match shouldn't be under-estimated) put on an ok 7 minute bout. Steiner only botched one move (a powerbomb) that I could see, while Test is finally improving in the ring. It's a shame it has been so gradual & he struggles to add to his repertoire though. Good finish & I pray this feud is over, but I don't think it is. Match Rating...6RANDY ORTON defeated SHAWN MICHAELS: It was very hard to pick a 'Match of the Night' at Unforgiven, and this bout could definitely stake a claim. It wasn't far off being very good, put it that way. It just lacked a little in pacing & had too few spots for a 19 minute match. HBK is still putting on great matches against practically any opponent, while Orton is another who is gradually improving. I didn't mind the finish with Flair's shenanigans causing a restart to the bout. Match Rating...7TRISH STRATUS & LITA defeated MOLLY HOLLY & GAIL KIM: Disappointing. For the amount of apparent hate that the heels had here, there was not enough intensity. For Lita's big return to wrestling, there was not enough excitement. The rematch the next night was a lot better. At least this was kept relatively short at 7 minutes. Man, compare Lita's moonsault to Kurt Angle's & you would think they were 2 completely different moves. Match Rating...5KANE defeated SHANE McMAHON in a Last Man Standing Match: Some will call this the match of the night, even though I don't recall seeing too many wrestling holds being applied. Obviously very spotty, this bout was fairly well choreographed & decently performed. The booking which saw Shane control most of the match was puzzling though. As I predicted last week, McMahon climbed the entrance-way & threw himself off of it. Unfortunately for him, Kane rolled out the way to become the last man standing at the 20 minute mark. Match Rating...7CHRISTIAN defeated ROB VAN DAM & CHRIS JERICHO to Retain the InterContinetal Title: If I had to choose one bout, I'd probably choose this as the match of the night. That is despite it not really flowing well for almost half of it's length. The first 10 minutes saw Jericho & Christian's allegiance last way too long, and I was starting to think that the WWE made a huge mistake in not having a singles match here. But the following 9 minutes was well put together, fairly unpredictable & had something for everyone. Christian pins RVD to retain the title & hopefully we will get to see a decent feud between these two. Match Rating...7AL SNOW & JONATHAN COACHMAN defeated JERRY LAWLER & JIM ROSS to become the Raw Commentators: You know you're in trouble when the first move of the match is practically botched!!! The WWE foolishly chose to have no commentators during this bout, and that unfortunately just made this 8 minute match drag out even more. I'm a fan of Al Snow, but it's been a while since he even wrestled on ppv. The only positive that existed for mine is that it could have been worse!!! The heels win following interference from Jericho. Match Rating...3BILL GOLDBERG defeated TRIPLE H to Win the World HeavyWeight Title: Satisfactory main event that was pretty much 'by the numbers'. At 15 minutes, the length of the match was about right. The intensity of the 2 combatants was sufficient, and while nothing really memorable happened, nothing disastrous occurred either. I would have preferred for the ending to be a little less abrupt, as it didn't really give a chance for the crowd to go nuts for a title change. It wasn't inspiring, but at least Raw finally crowned a new champ. Match Rating...6PPV RATING (46/80) = 58Looking at the key, I have given Unforgiven a 'C' grade & have said that it was 'Average'. Right on, if I do say so myself. It only got one extra rating point over the previous Raw pay-per-view, Bad Blood, and that my friends is not a good thing. Apart from the commentators match, there wasn't anything too disastrous or embarrassing about this event, but when you have to toss up between 3 ok matches as your match of the night, you know you're in trouble. Nothing stood out whatsoever!!! This is pay-per-view for goodness sake; Reward the purchaser. Oh well, there's always a SmackDown pay-per-view just around the corner.

reviewText: WWEUNFORGIVEN 2003This was the sixth Unforgiven if I am not mistaken and happened in a state I once spent many moons in, Pennsylvania. It would be the event that would see Triple H finally beaten for the World title and when Shane O Mac took a big leap of faith.1.[ TAG TEAM TITLE TABLE MATCH]THE DUDLEY BOYZ VS LA RESISTANCE & ROB CONWAY-the first match of the night was going to be a six man tag match but Spike was attacked and injured. So Steve Austin made this for the tag team titles. This was an excellent choice for an opening match as tag matches usually work out that way. The action was good here and picks up as it goes eventually transforming into everyone in the ring at once. The action picks up once the tables come out and La Resistance and Conway take rides threw tables.2.SCOTT STEINER VS TEST-this match was for the services of Stacy Keibler and if Scott were to lose he would work for Test. As one would expect this was not the best match of the night but still it was good. The story here really made this match for me and Stacy's involvement throughout added to it. This may have been their best match in the feud, I'd have to go back and watch them all. This is a power vs. power matchup with each trying to show the other up. The ending made sense with Stacy dictating the finish by accidently laying out Scott. He then eats a big boot from Test and test gets the victory.3.SHAWN MICHAELS VS RANDY ORTON-this was the Legend vs. Legend killer match and may be my favorite of the night. The match moves at a quick pace with HBK really taking control. Ric Flair's involvement is great throughout the match. Some people didn't like the ending but I thought it was great for both guys really. Shawn lands the sweet chin music and gets the three count but Flair puts Orton's foot on the rope. This makes the ref restart it and Randy gets the victory right after.4.MOLLY HOLLY & GAIL KIM VS TRISH STRATUS & LITA-this was Lita's first match back in a while and this was also when the women's matches in WWE were good on a regular basis. This was a good match with some good back and forth action but of course Trish and Lita get the win after Lita does her moonsault. I remember I was all about Molly and Gail winning.5.[LAST MAN STANDING]SHANE MCMAHON VS KANE-this was a crazy math right here but any time Shane is in a match you can bet it will be. He like his dad will take crazy bumps and do crazy spots to entertain. Kane is the powerhouse but Shane looks really good throughout this match. His coast to coast is a highlight but it is his jump that people remember from this. Too bad Kane moved and got the win since Shane was only in this match to avenge his mother Linda.6.[I-C TITLE]CHRISTIAN VS CHRIS JERICHO VS RVD-another really good match with all three guys looking good here. Each man gets in his own spots and because it was a three way match the action moves at a fast pace. These are three of my favorites ever so I knew this match was going to be good. At first Christian and Y2J had an alliance but that would not last. In the end Christian keeps the title in a really good match.7.JERRY LAWLER & JIM ROSS VS AL SNOW & COACH-this was the match to see who would be the commentators for Raw. Most of the match is spent between Lawler and Snow and rightfully so since they are the wrestlers. Coach has more time than Ross but it is Ross that gets the biggest reaction from the crowd when tagged in. Y2J hits Ross with a dropkick from behind to cost him and Lawler the match.8.[WORLD TITLE]TRIPLE H VS GOLDBERG-this was the match that would be title vs. career, if Goldberg lost he was done. But the thing was Triple H could lose the belt by pinfall, sub, count out, or even DQ, so that added to the intrigue of the match. Now this is far from a classic match and not either mans best match but it is not as bad as some say. At the time I thought this was going to be a great match and it turned out to be a good one. The action is all about the power moves from both men really and Triple H breaks out the sledgehammer. Still Goldberg nails him with the spear and then the jackhammer, from sledge to jack, I like it.This was far from the best event of that year but it still had some good matches on it. Plus it would lead to  many other things happening storyline wise. Over all I liked this event and would recommend it to any wrestling fan. Besides it has HBK in it so it all good with me.

reviewText: This was a RAW only PPV brand held in Hershey, PA. To be honest, there was really only two matches worth watching on this program: The triple threat intercontinental championship match, and HBK vs Randy Orton.-Six-Man Tables Match for the World Tag Team ChampionshipLa Resistance (c) and Rob Conway vs The Dudley Boyz. This converts over to a handicap 3-on-2 Table Match due to the events on HEAT. **/*****- Scott Steiner vs TestBasically, if Scotty wins, he gets Stacy in his corner forever, and if he loses, Test gets not only Stacy, but Steiner has to give up his services as well. Steiner isn't half as bad as everyone makes him out to be, and actually pulled off a good match here. ***/*****- Lita and Trish Stratus vs Molly Holly and Gail KimThis is Lita's return match after being out for a little over a year. Some good moves by Lita, Trish, and Gail, but Molly seemed a little lethargic in this match. **/*****- Christian (c) vs Rob Van Dam vs Chris JerichoTriple Threat Match for the Intercontinental Championship. This match saved this PPV from being a total flop. Three highly talented men, all with different styles, make for a great match. Christian is highly underrated in my opinion, but he has all the tools in the business. ****/*****- Shawn Michaels HBK vs Randy OrtonMade out to be a Legend vs Legend Killer match, this was the only other good match on the card. One man who has done it all in this business, and another who has just started. Michaels hasn't lost too much of a step since his prime, and Orton looked amazing. ****/*****- Kane vs ShaneThis match was typically a hardcore match, except instead of a three count, the ref must count to ten before the wrestler can stand up. Typical hardcore style match, boring, up until the end. I won't give it away, but it's great. **/*****-J.R. and Jerry 'The King' Lawler vs Coach and SnowRAW announcing job on the line. This was just garbage time, and really had no point. These days, I'm all for longer matches, but this was should have been shorter. No commentary made it even worse. */*****-HHH (c) vs GoldbergWorld Heavyweight Championship Match. HHH can lose the title on ANY circumstances (count out, DQ, pin, submission). If Goldberg loses, he is out of the business forever. Not just WWE, but the entire business, meaning he cannot go anywhere else. Very short match for a championship match, nothing spectacular here, but it does start to pick up a little towards the end. However it's just not long enough. **/*****

reviewText: Pretty good PPV, although it looked a lot better on paper.1. La Resistance & Rob Conway vs. Dudley Boys (World Tag Titles/Table Match)Good way to kick off the PPV.  Dudley Boys put on great table matches.  Good bumps taken by all, especially the over-the-top rope table bump by Rob Conway.  Good match.  (8/10)2. Scott Steiner vs. Test (Winner Gets Stacey Kiebler's Services)This was the final match of the long lasting fued between these two.  This was the best match out of all them.  Great video clip before the match.  There are a lot of near falls in the match.  Good ending.  Probably Steiner's best match in the WWE.  (7.5/10)3. Shawn Michaels vs. Randy OrtonThis was Randy Orton's first great fued and first great match in the WWE.  This was the beginning of his rise to the top of the company.  Great match.  (8.5/10)4. Lita & Trish Stratus vs. Molly Holly & Gail KimActually, not a bad women's match.  (6/10)5. Kane vs. Shane McMahon (Last Man Standing Match)Wow!  Great performance by the two competitors.  This was a great fued.  Good bumps by both men.  Shane delivers the Van Daminator with the ring steps to Kane.  Good shot by Shane with the camera on Kane.  Shane goes to the top of the set design and attempts to hit Kane with an elbow off the top.  Amazing.  (9/10)6. Chris Jericho vs. Kane vs. Rob Van Dam (Intercontinental Title/Triple Threat)Very good match.  It was just to bad the crowd was dead because they were still in shock from the last match.  Great spot with the triple top rope suplex.  Surprise ending.  (8/10)7. Jim Ross & Jerry Lawler vs. The Coach & Al Snow (Winner Is Becomes Announcers of RAW)Why did they do this?  Horrible match, and horrible outcome.  (3/10)8. Goldberg vs. Triple H (World Heavyweight Title/If Goldberg Loses He Must Leave the WWE)Not the best match.  Triple H was still hurt for this match.  Nothing really happens worth noting.  (7/10)Good effort by the RAW brand.  Pick this DVD up for the Shane/Kane match.  It is worth it.Overall Rating:  8/10

reviewText: 1. Two on three tables match Dudley Boys vs. La Resistance & Rob Conway: This was a good match. I'm a big fan of table matches, especially when they are elimination like this one is. There were so many hardcore and wrestling moments in this match. 8/102. Scott Steiner vs. Test: I felt this match should have saved for Raw. One reason it wasn't to exciting to watch. Also, I didn't like the ending very much either. 4/103. HBK vs. Randy Orton: This was a good match. This was at the beginning of Randy Orton's career and this is basically where it took off. Also this is were he got the nickname of the legend killer. 7/104. Lita & Trish Stratus vs. Molly Holly & Gail Kim: This was another good divas match. The only bad part the women's title wasn't being defending that night. But this match consisted of arguably the best divas in the WWE at the time. 5/105. Kane vs. Shane McMahon Last Man Standing Match: My favorite match of the night. This match was not fought in the ring the whole which is a good thing, plus it didn't end in the ring either. A lot of weapons were used in this match. The ending was shocking and my most favorite part of the whole ppv, and this was not the first time that ever happened either.9/106.Chris Jericho vs. Christian vs. Rob Van Dam Triple Treat Match for I.C title: This was a great match. Three great superstars for the title. It acted like a handicap match at some points two, but the other guy held his ground. 7/107.J.R & Jerry Lawler vs. Al Snow & Jonathan Coachmen: This match was pointless. I'm not even going to talk about the stipulation because got changed soon after. 3/108.HHH vs. Goldberg for World Heavyweight Title: This was a good title match. Had great wrestling and exciting moments. The two best of Raw going at it for the title was a good idea with a good backround story to it. 9/10Overall: I would get this ppv. But there are some exceptions. I would get it for the hardcore part not much for the other matches. But don't get me wrong the other matches were still good just hardcore makes it more entertaining. That's just my opinion and no one else's.

reviewText: I have been a wrestling fan since 1996 and have watched all kinds of wrestling. I have a wrestling DVD/VHS collection spanning over 50 all together. This is the most complete and accurate review of this DVD you will find. I hope you find this review helpful; remember to vote helpful or not helpful. (Note-Each DVD I review has a "Match of the DVD" award somewhere in it.)WWE Unforgiven 2003After watching Unforgiven, I have mixed emotions about this edition. Some of the matches are top notch; others are horrendous. I love the theme song, which is Enemy by Sevendust. The DVD had no extras to talk of. The event itself probably is not worth buying, but you might want to check it out for a few select matches.Handicap Table MatchWorld Tag Team ChampionshipsDudley Boyz VS La Resistance(c) & Rob ConwayThe set-up to this match was that all members of the team had to be put through a table before a winner could be declared. Members could stay in the match until it was over though. The match itself was average, but the table spots are nice. Conway takes a brutal spot, being thrown over the ropes through a table.RATING- 6.5/10Winner Gets Stacy Keibler's ServicesTest VS Scott SteinerI actually enjoyed the story moving into this match. The highlight video before the match really got me into the match. The match itself is not much though. Stacy want Steiner to win, and eventually interferes in the match. You probably will not watch this more than once.RATING- 6/10Randy Orton VS Shawn MichaelsWe have just reached the first awesome match of the evening. This is one of Orton's first Legend VS Legend Killer matches. There is a lot of good wrestling, and HBK hits a huge cross body splash to the outside. The ending is weird and I feel it hurt the match a lot.RATING- 8.5/10Gal Kim & Molly Holly VS Lita & TrishThis is Gail Kim's first PPV match. This is also Lita's first PPV match back after spinal surgery. This was a solid encounter, but the crowd does not seem that into it. Lita puts on a good performance.RATING- 5/10Last Man Standing Match (Match of the DVD)Kane VS Shane McMahonInsane. That is the only word that can describe this match. Actually, I lied. Let me give you a few more words. The match has a very slow pace to it, and at the beginning does not seem that great. The match picks up over time and becomes a match full of sick spots. Shane hits a glorious Coast to Coast into steel steps. The ending features Shane falling thirty-five feet.RATING- 9/10Intercontinental ChampionshipY2J VS Christian(c) VS Rob Van DamI thought that this was another well-put together match. The problem was that the crowd did not care much after the previous match. There is a ton of highflying maneuvers, and some solid wrestling. Most of the match is fought between two men, instead of three. There is a huge Tower of Doom spot.RATING- 7/10Winners Commentates RawJim Ross & Jerry Lawler VS Coach & Al SnowThere is no commentary for this match, and the crowd is dead again. You can hear echoes every now and then. The match is primarily fought between Lawler and Snow, but Coach gets a good amount of ring time. Jim Ross only gets in the ring at the end. It brought a smile to my face to see that he was enjoying himself. Jericho makes an appearance toward the end.RATING- 3/10World Heavyweight ChampionshipTriple H(c) VS GoldbergAs far as Main Event matches go, this sucked. It was fun to see Triple H finally dethroned, but it was the wrong man to do it. Triple H works on the legs of Goldberg, because Goldberg is lethal when he is standing. The match is short as well.RATING- 6/10

reviewText: Dudley boyz vs French guys-Exellent tables match and a great opener.It was good to see all 3 members of La resistance go through tables.3D THE FROGS 8/10Steiner vs Test-Stacy was HOT as usual but to bad she has to go with Test.Stacys chair shot on steiner by mistake helped Test win with a big boot.This match was better than their one at Bad Blood but still not the best match up. 6/10HBK vs Randy Orton-Legend vs legend killer.Why does everybody say that Flair ruins this match.I think it made it more entertaining.Good technical wrestling match between a legend and a future legend.HBK wins and his music hits but the ref see's Ortons foot on the rope.Flair gives Orton the brasp nut and oron wins by cracking Michaels in the face several times.10/10 MatchLita/Trish vs Jealous Jesabells-Lita makes her return in style by pinning Molly after a lita sault.Okay match for womans standards but the second worst match of the night. 5/10Shane vs Kane-Last man standing-Lots of weapons lots of action over 20 minutes long wonderful match best of the night.Shane did some entertaining things but that 50 m jump at the end was just stupidity. 10/10Christian vs Jericho vs RVD-Alright match but dull at times.RVD did his best to entertain but Christian is boring and Jericho was off his game that night.Christian retains by using the championship belt.7/10JR/King vs Coach/Al Snow-boring with no commentators and I cant believe we had to listen to Coaches voice every Monday night on Raw.Jericho screws JR. 4/10TRIPLE H VS GOLDBERG-New champion the game has lost his title which he won at Armageddon 2002.GAME OVER.Good match between 2 big bulls.Triple H couldnt even win with a sledge Hammer.Goldberg beat the game once again with the spear followed by the Jackhammer. 7/10Unforgiven was the 2nd best pay per veiw in 2003 after Wrestlemania 19 in my opinion.It had matches with alot on the line and it was truly unforgiving.

reviewText: This PPV was quite unique, J.R. & The King vs. Coach & Al Snow, Kane Vs. Shane McMahon in a last man standing match, A Table Match & Everything on the line in the main event between Goldberg & the man who has had the World Title for the past few eons, HHH. Goldberg finally won the world title as HHH finally after nine months of waiting for it to happen, lost it. This had some great moments and was another great Raw-only ppv event, Shane's huge fall off the titan tron was really big and all of the other action capped off by Goldberg's title win made this one hell of a ppv.
